# NextJS App Structure

This project uses Next.js App Router with the following key directories:

## Routing Structure

- [app/[locale]](mdc:app/[locale]): Main app routes with internationalization support
- [app/api](mdc:app/api): API routes for backend functionality
- [pages/](mdc:pages): Any legacy pages using the Pages Router (if any exist)

## App Architecture

- [app/context](mdc:app/context): React context providers specific to the app directory
- [app/components](mdc:app/components): Components that are specific to the app directory
- [context/](mdc:context): Global context providers used throughout the application
- [hooks/](mdc:hooks): Custom React hooks

## Configuration

- [next.config.ts](mdc:next.config.ts): Next.js configuration
- [tailwind.config.ts](mdc:tailwind.config.ts): Tailwind CSS configuration
- [tsconfig.json](mdc:tsconfig.json): TypeScript configuration
- [middleware.ts](mdc:middleware.ts): Next.js middleware for handling requests
